## SECTION C: OPERATORS (15 Questions)

### Arithmetic Questions (26-30)

**Q26.** Calculate compound interest:
```
Principal = 10000
Rate = 5% per year
Time = 2 years
Formula: Amount = P * (1 + R/100)^T
Calculate and print the final amount and interest earned.
Q27. A pizza costs Rs. 250. If you order 4 pizzas, you get 15% discount. Calculate:

Cost without discount
Discount amount
Final cost

Q28. Given a 3-digit number (e.g., 456), extract and print each digit separately using arithmetic operators (%, //).
Q29. Convert:

150 minutes to hours and minutes
3665 seconds to hours, minutes, and seconds
Use // and % operators.

Q30. A car travels at 60 km/h. Calculate:

Distance in 2.5 hours
Time needed to travel 450 km
Speed needed to cover 300 km in 4 hours

Comparison Questions (31-33)
Q31. Compare two students:
student1_marks = 85
student2_marks = 92
Print who scored higher, if they're equal, and the difference in marks.
Q32. Check voting eligibility:
age = 17
Print whether person can vote (age >= 18). Also check if they're a senior citizen (age >= 60).
Q33. Compare two products:
product1_price = 1500
product1_rating = 4.5
product2_price = 1200
product2_rating = 4.2
Determine which product has better rating AND lower price.
Logical Operators Questions (34-37)
Q34. Library access system: A person can enter if they have a membership OR they're a student. They must also have valid ID. Create variables and check access.
has_membership = False
is_student = True
has_id = True
Q35. College admission criteria:

Marks >= 80 OR
Marks >= 70 AND sports quota
Must have passing grade (>= 40)

Given marks=75 and sports_quota=True, check eligibility.
Q36. Online shopping discount:

10% off if purchase > 1000
Additional 5% if customer is premium member
No discount if cart < 500

Calculate final price for: cart_value=1200, is_premium=True
Q37. Password validation:

Length >= 8
Contains at least one number
Not equal to username

Given: username="user123", password="pass1234", check if valid (you can use in operator).
Assignment Operators Questions (38-40)
Q38. Start with score = 0. Update it through a game:

Collect coin: +10
Kill enemy: +50
Complete level: +100
Get hit: -20
Use power-up: *2

Use compound operators (+=, -=, *=). Print score after each action.
Q39. Bank account simulation:
balance = 5000
Perform these operations using compound operators:

Deposit 2000
Withdraw 1500
Interest earned (5% of current balance)
Withdrawal fee (2% of last withdrawal)
Print balance after each operation.

Q40. Step counter app:
total_steps = 0
```
Update steps throughout the day:
- Morning walk: 2000 steps
- Afternoon: 1500 steps
- Evening: 3000 steps
